				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm not sure it will work well, there is a race condition between the decoder disable speed and the shift register propagation + data register setup time. The decoder should win this condition because disable is fast, but it's possible it won't. The point is that this logic is correct, and design can definitely be made stable by making all registers synchronous to /ROMSEL. To do this the data registers need to be "enable" type maser-slave flip-flops with a MUX selecting D or Q. Perhaps Nintendo took this route, but it uses a lot of gates / bit.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

