				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm pretty sure it's A).
<br />
<br />I mean, I don't see how ignoring the second consecutive write would prevent anyone to pirate MMC1 games.
<br />
<br />Using the inc $xxxx instruction on a ROM adress that contains a value &gt;$80 seems to be the standard way to reset the MMC1, almost all games I've checked do it this way.
<br />
<br />I think the face some games that do the tricky double writes just did a inc instruction on a place that contained a $ff value was pure randomness, and that since it worked they kept it this way and didn't even realize a $00 was written to the MMC1 but ignored.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
